Date: Mon, 22 Apr 2013 18:12:39 -0500
Subject: [PATCH 076/248] FogBugz #116352: Disable the 2nd I2C port on devkit

On the SOCFPGA devkit, only 1 I2C port is enabled.

[Original patch taken from
git://git.rocketboards.org/linux-socfpga.git socfpga-3.14]

Signed-off-by: Yanjiang Jin <yanjiang.jin@windriver.com>
Signed-off-by: Dinh Nguyen <dinguyen@altera.com>
---
 arch/arm/boot/dts/socfpga_cyclone5.dtsi | 4 ++++
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+)

diff --git a/arch/arm/boot/dts/socfpga_cyclone5.dtsi b/arch/arm/boot/dts/socfpga_cyclone5.dtsi
index 169ed12..aa319e9 100644
--- a/arch/arm/boot/dts/socfpga_cyclone5.dtsi
+++ b/arch/arm/boot/dts/socfpga_cyclone5.dtsi
@@ -88,6 +88,10 @@
 			status = "okay";
 		};
 
+		i2c1: i2c@ffc05000 {
+			status = "disabled";
+		};
+
 		qspi: spi@ff705000 {
 				compatible = "cadence,qspi";
 				#address-cells = <1>;
